Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.13,0:00:02.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,大家好，我是Tim Dodd，欢迎观看本期的《每日宇航员》
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.13,0:00:02.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Hi it's me, Tim Dodd, the Everyday Astronaut
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.50,0:00:07.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉的猎鹰九号火箭——世界上第一个可复用火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:00:02.50,0:00:07.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,SpaceX's Falcon 9 rocket, the world's first reusable rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.57,0:00:08.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,停一下！
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.57,0:00:08.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 1,0:00:08.70,0:00:09.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不对吧
Dialogue: 2,0:00:08.70,0:00:09.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,No it's not
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.53,0:00:10.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还记得航天飞机吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.53,0:00:10.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the Space Shuttle?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.93,0:00:16.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机的轨道器和固体火箭助推器都是可复用的不是吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.93,0:00:16.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It had those Solid Rocket Boosters, and the Orbiter which were both reusable weren't they?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.14,0:00:21.63,1080CN,,0,0,0,,今天我们就来谈谈，为啥航天飞机就没法实现真正意义的复用
Dialogue: 2,0:00:16.14,0:00:21.63,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Well today we're going to talk about why the Space Shuttle failed to actually be reusable
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.63,0:00:25.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也引入一个更准确的表述，可翻新的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.63,0:00:25.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and wound up being described with a more accurate word, refurbishable
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.88,0:00:28.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到处都能见到有人拿航天飞机的毛病
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.88,0:00:28.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,People often cite the shortcomings of the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.73,0:00:33.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,去把太空叉的猎鹰九号批判一番
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.73,0:00:33.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and are quick to point it to SpaceX's claims of the Falcon 9 booster being reusable
Dialogue: 1,0:00:33.07,0:00:38.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以今天我们来看看
Dialogue: 2,0:00:33.07,0:00:38.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So today we're going to look at what it takes to get the Space Shuttle operational between flights
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.10,0:00:41.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号究竟是凭借着什么才能每次发射进退自如
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.10,0:00:41.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,what it takes to get a Falcon 9 operational between flights
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.06,0:00:45.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,为啥太空叉的一级火箭能比太空飞机高到不知哪里去
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.06,0:00:45.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and why SpaceX's first stage booster take much less of a beating than the Space Shuttle did
Dialogue: 1,0:00:45.89,0:00:47.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,顺便还要回顾一下
Dialogue: 2,0:00:45.89,0:00:47.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,We'll also do a quick reminder
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.54,0:00:50.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉为了让Block 5的一级能达成目标
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.54,0:00:50.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,of what technologies SpaceX added to their Block 5 booster
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.77,0:00:55.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,往上面又加了什么新技术
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.77,0:00:55.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to hopefully achieve their goal of making a rapidly reusable rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.00,0:01:00.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以至于就算没做什么大修，它也能被射个10次
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.00,0:01:00.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that can truly be reused 10 times before needing any kind of serious refurbishment
Dialogue: 1,0:01:00.21,0:01:01.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,走你！
Dialogue: 2,0:01:00.21,0:01:01.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Let's get started!
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.14,0:01:03.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,- 3, 2, 1, 0
Dialogue: 2,0:01:01.14,0:01:03.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- Three, two, one, zero
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.49,0:01:04.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,起飞！
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.49,0:01:04.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and lift off
Dialogue: 1,0:01:04.94,0:01:07.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这是人类的一小步
Dialogue: 2,0:01:04.94,0:01:07.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- That's one small step for man
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.45,0:01:15.74,1080CN,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问，可复用是如今航天界最热的词
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.45,0:01:15.74,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- Reusable is definitely the hottest buzz word in the new space industry
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.74,0:01:19.97,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果你不知道为什么这概念能引领时代
Dialogue: 2,0:01:15.74,0:01:19.97,1080EN,,0,0,0,,If you don't know why a vehicle being reusable is such a massive game changer
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.97,0:01:23.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我建议你看看我过往视频叫《为啥重型猎鹰很重要》
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.97,0:01:23.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,may I suggest checking out my video Why does Falcon Heavy matter
Dialogue: 1,0:01:23.46,0:01:27.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,深入浅出解释可复用性的重要性
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.46,0:01:27.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to help get a good perspective on why reusability matters
Dialogue: 1,0:01:27.01,0:01:31.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,长话短说就是发挥空间太小
Dialogue: 2,0:01:27.01,0:01:31.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the margins to get stuff to space are so thin
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.61,0:01:35.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,把那么多东西射上天需要巨大的火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.61,0:01:35.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it takes a massive rocket to put anything substantial up there
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.98,0:01:42.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因此基本没有多余的重量让你安装回收装置了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.98,0:01:42.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So unfortunately there's just too little margins left over to add additional hardware to make a rocket reusable
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.49,0:01:46.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这就会让航天变得超级、无比、极其昂贵
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.49,0:01:46.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This makes spaceflight extremely, extremely expensive
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.73,0:01:54.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以至于把成本降到每千克”仅1000美金“都只能是期望
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.73,0:01:54.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As in, so expensive we're hoping to someday see costs come down to "just a $1000" per kilogram!
Dialogue: 1,0:01:54.92,0:01:58.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,想象一下你在地球上遇到了这种水平的运费
Dialogue: 2,0:01:54.92,0:01:58.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Yeah, imagine those shipping costs down here on Earth
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.38,0:02:03.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,喂，你那订个伊兰特的轮胎要多少钱啊？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.38,0:02:03.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Hi there, I'm calling to get a quote for some new tires for my 2011 Hyundai Elantra
Dialogue: 1,0:02:03.93,0:02:06.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,废话当然是GT款
Dialogue: 2,0:02:03.93,0:02:06.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Yes of course it's the GT model
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.07,0:02:09.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我在地上漂移摩擦和地面保持零距离
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.07,0:02:09.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I did some really cool drifting and so that's why the tires are bad
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.50,0:02:11.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到底要多少钱啊？
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.50,0:02:11.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,How much would the new tires be?
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.73,0:02:13.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,才400刀？
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.73,0:02:13.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Oh $400?
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.36,0:02:15.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,邮费多少啊？
Dialogue: 2,0:02:13.36,0:02:15.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,How much for shipping?
Dialogue: 1,0:02:15.46,0:02:18.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,三万六？？？
Dialogue: 2,0:02:15.46,0:02:18.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,$36000!
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.11,0:02:25.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但是相比先前往天上射东西的价格，这跟包邮没两样
Dialogue: 2,0:02:18.11,0:02:25.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And{\fs33} that would actually be a steal compared to the historically astronomical prices of getting space hardware into space
Dialogue: 1,0:02:25.50,0:02:31.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就算是历史最低价，也得要3000刀左右才能运个1千克
Dialogue: 2,0:02:25.50,0:02:31.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Even the cheapest dollar to kilogram ratio is around the $3000 per kilogram mark
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.23,0:02:33.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就这还完全是靠猎鹰九号和重型猎鹰才压下来的价位
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.23,0:02:33.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,thanks to the Falcon 9 and Falcon Heavy
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.69,0:02:37.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,只能说还好火箭送快递目前还不是主流了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.69,0:02:37.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It's a good thing rocket delivery isn't the standard here on Earth
Dialogue: 1,0:02:37.22,0:02:39.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这就能解释为啥会需要可复用了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:37.22,0:02:39.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So here's where reusability comes in
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.81,0:02:42.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问！
Dialogue: 2,0:02:39.81,0:02:42.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It's honestly fundamental! Of course!
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.89,0:02:46.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,光是个引擎就几百上千万块钱的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.89,0:02:46.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Why throw away super expensive multi-million dollar engines
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.33,0:02:49.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,更别说还有箭身和一大堆零件
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.33,0:02:49.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and a massive fuselage and all that extra stuff
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.76,0:02:52.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你寻思我这旧火箭不要了？
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.76,0:02:52.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,when you could just reuse it, right?
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.29,0:02:54.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,对不起，我们是穷鬼
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.29,0:02:54.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I mean duh!
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.27,0:02:57.43,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这就是为啥要发明航天飞机了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.27,0:02:57.43,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Well that was the original idea for the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.43,0:02:58.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,信不信由你
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.43,0:02:58.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Believe it or not
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.31,0:03:01.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA早在人类登月之前
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.31,0:03:01.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA was seeking a reusable launch vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.07,0:03:03.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就已经想要这么个玩意了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.07,0:03:03.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,before we even put humans on the moon
Dialogue: 1,0:03:03.57,0:03:06.66,1080CN,,0,0,0,,研究开始于1968年
Dialogue: 2,0:03:03.57,0:03:06.66,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The original studies began in 1968
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.66,0:03:09.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,比阿姆斯特朗月球上那个著名的一小一大步
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.66,0:03:09.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,some 10 months before Neil Armstrong
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.03,0:03:11.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,早了差不多十个月
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.03,0:03:11.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,famously took the first steps on the moon
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.23,0:03:12.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,事实上
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.23,0:03:12.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact
Dialogue: 1,0:03:12.33,0:03:15.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机最初的飞行员，约翰·杨
Dialogue: 2,0:03:12.33,0:03:15.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,one of the first people to fly the Space Shuttle, John Young
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.48,0:03:18.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,接到航天飞机项目获批的消息时，正好在月面上行走
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.48,0:03:18.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,was walking on the moon when he got news of the shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.41,0:03:20.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,- 时候不错，我跟你说个好消息
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.41,0:03:20.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- This looks like a good time for some good news here
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.68,0:03:25.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,白宫277票比60票通过了航天预算审批
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.68,0:03:25.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The House passed the space budget yesterday, 277 to 60
Dialogue: 1,0:03:25.37,0:03:27.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当然也包括航天飞机的预算
Dialogue: 2,0:03:25.37,0:03:27.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which includes the votes for the shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.07,0:03:31.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,- 流批，太棒了!
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.07,0:03:31.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- That's wonderful, wonderful
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.58,0:03:33.63,1080CN,,0,0,0,,Tony我跟你讲
Dialogue: 2,0:03:32.58,0:03:33.63,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- Tony, again I'll say it, with that salute
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.63,0:03:36.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,身为美国人真吼哇！
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.63,0:03:36.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I'm proud to be an American
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.81,0:03:40.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,多好的项目，多好的地点，多好的经历！
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.81,0:03:40.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you, what a program and what a place and what an experience
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.42,0:03:42.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所言极是
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.42,0:03:42.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, and I'll say it too
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.24,0:03:43.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我也会这么说
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.24,0:03:43.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- So am I
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.07,0:03:44.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我们的国家渴望航天飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.07,0:03:44.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Country needs that shuttle mighty bad
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.92,0:03:47.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但事情的结果却与期望恰恰相反
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.92,0:03:47.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,- So with all the excitement leading up to the shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.67,0:03:49.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,回到50年后的今天
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.67,0:03:49.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,fast forward 50 years to today
Dialogue: 1,0:03:49.76,0:03:53.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,人们对航天飞机的态度转向了相反的方向
Dialogue: 2,0:03:49.76,0:03:53.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the Space Shuttle has kind of a bad taste in our mouths
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.28,0:03:57.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,且不说贵上了天，安全性也得不到保障
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.28,0:03:57.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It wound up being terribly expensive, pretty dangerous
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.07,0:04:01.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,论成本，它称第二，没人敢称第一，第三差了十万八千里
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.07,0:04:01.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and actually more expensive than just about any other way to get into space
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.95,0:04:05.26,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尽管有些实验只能在航天飞机上操作，所以也不能说毫无意义
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.95,0:04:05.26,1080EN,,0,0,0,,although it could do things that no other launch vehicle could do
Dialogue: 1,0:04:05.26,0:04:08.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以，一堆世界上最高级的大脑设计出来的航天器
Dialogue: 2,0:04:05.26,0:04:08.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So with some of the greatest minds working on the shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:04:08.24,0:04:11.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,咋还是没法按预期那样把成本降下来呢
Dialogue: 2,0:04:08.24,0:04:11.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,why did it fail its promise of bringing the cost down?
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.34,0:04:16.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉是命中注定要复现历史，还是50年来早已天翻地覆？
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.34,0:04:16.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Is SpaceX doomed to repeat history or has a lot changed in 50 years?
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.27,0:04:20.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先，对比一下两者的回收系统
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.27,0:04:20.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So first, let's look at the recovery methods of each system
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.24,0:04:22.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这里就能体现出相当多的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.24,0:04:22.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They're quite different
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.15,0:04:27.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机的回收主要依靠降落伞和升力体机身
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.15,0:04:27.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Space Shuttle utilized both parachutes and a lifting body to recover hardware
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.55,0:04:29.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以我们依次看看回收的都有啥
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.55,0:04:29.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Let's go in order of what was recovered
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.29,0:04:31.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先是固体助推器
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.29,0:04:31.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so starting with the Solid Rocket Boosters
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.76,0:04:34.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,大概起飞两分钟后被直接抛弃
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.76,0:04:34.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which were jettisoned around two minutes into flight
Dialogue: 1,0:04:34.35,0:04:40.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,助推器大概在4800km/h的速度时从航天器分离
Dialogue: 2,0:04:34.35,0:04:40.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The boosters separate while traveling around 4800 kilometers an hour or 3000 miles an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:04:40.24,0:04:43.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,高度大约45公里
Dialogue: 2,0:04:40.24,0:04:43.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,at an altitude of around 45 kilometers or 30 miles
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.92,0:04:50.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,之后还会因为速度一直上升到65公里的高度
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.92,0:04:50.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And due to their velocity they continue to coast upward to their highest point of around 65 kilometers or 40 miles
Dialogue: 1,0:04:50.61,0:04:54.26,1080CN,,0,0,0,,顺便，这也就是说那些固体助推器
Dialogue: 2,0:04:50.61,0:04:54.26,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Just a fun note that does means the SRBs never actually make it
Dialogue: 1,0:04:54.26,0:04:58.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从来都没有到过卡门线，也就是说从来都没出过大气层
Dialogue: 2,0:04:54.26,0:04:58.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,above the Karman line or the commonly agreed upon boundary of space
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.75,0:05:00.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,记好咯
Dialogue: 2,0:04:58.75,0:05:00.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So keep that in mind
Dialogue: 1,0:05:00.48,0:05:02.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,助推器穿过大气层
Dialogue: 2,0:05:00.48,0:05:02.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The boosters fall back through the atmosphere
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.52,0:05:09.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在4786米的高度，开始放出一连串的降落伞
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.52,0:05:09.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and start popping a sequence of parachutes at exactly 4786 meters or 15704 feet
Dialogue: 1,0:05:11.41,0:05:14.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,先是引导伞，接着是减速伞
Dialogue: 2,0:05:11.41,0:05:14.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Eventually after a pilot chute, and a drogue chute
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.46,0:05:16.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后放出三个主伞
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.46,0:05:16.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the three main parachutes deploy
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.33,0:05:20.19,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后溅落海面，还算是软着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.33,0:05:20.19,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and splish splash the booster down relatively softly in the ocean
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.19,0:05:24.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,另一方面的轨道器，就比两个助推器啊，跑得还快
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.19,0:05:24.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Orbiter on the other hand is traveling much, much faster
Dialogue: 1,0:05:24.21,0:05:29.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以这玩意的回收进程，就要火热得多
Dialogue: 2,0:05:24.21,0:05:29.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and its recovery, like all orbital things, is a lot hotter
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.60,0:05:33.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,提前一个小时，就要来个大转身
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.60,0:05:33.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,About one hour before touchdown, the Orbiter turns around
Dialogue: 1,0:05:33.95,0:05:37.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,屁股朝前脸向后
Dialogue: 2,0:05:33.95,0:05:37.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and faces away from its direction of travel or prograde
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.41,0:05:43.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,启动轨道机动系统（OMS），降低1%的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.41,0:05:43.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It fires up its orbital maneuvering system or OMS and slows down 1%
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.46,0:05:46.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,对，你没听错，就是只有1%！
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.46,0:05:46.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Yep, that's it, only about 1%!
Dialogue: 1,0:05:46.72,0:05:48.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过这也完全足够
Dialogue: 2,0:05:46.72,0:05:48.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And that's enough to lower its orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.34,0:05:51.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,将飞机的轨道从480公里
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.34,0:05:51.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,from about 480 kilometers or 300 miles
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.62,0:05:56.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,降低到最低点只有45千米的轨道上
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.62,0:05:56.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,down to just 45 kilometers or 28 miles at its lowest point
Dialogue: 1,0:05:56.63,0:05:57.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,Crazy个头，玩过KSP都懂
Dialogue: 2,0:05:56.63,0:05:57.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That's crazy
Dialogue: 1,0:05:57.77,0:05:59.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后呢这个航天飞机还要再转个身
Dialogue: 2,0:05:57.77,0:05:59.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Orbiter then turns back around
Dialogue: 1,0:05:59.52,0:06:02.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,头朝前，保持约40度仰角
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.52,0:06:02.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so it can reenter at about a 40 degree angle
Dialogue: 1,0:06:02.50,0:06:05.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,接下来就是靠大气层的工作了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.50,0:06:05.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now it's time for the atmosphere to do its work
Dialogue: 1,0:06:05.11,0:06:08.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这时候航天飞机还是巡航在这个轨道上
Dialogue: 2,0:06:05.11,0:06:08.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Orbiter is absolutely cruising at this point
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.22,0:06:13.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,依然保持着大约27000km/h的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.22,0:06:13.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It's still traveling around 27000 kilometers an hour or 17000 miles an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.58,0:06:15.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,接着，空气分子开始撞击我们的飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.58,0:06:15.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the Orbiter begins to hit air molecules
Dialogue: 1,0:06:15.64,0:06:18.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,产生极大的摩擦力
Dialogue: 2,0:06:15.64,0:06:18.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and starts to build up a ton of friction
Dialogue: 1,0:06:18.88,0:06:20.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也就产生了极大的热量
Dialogue: 2,0:06:18.88,0:06:20.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and therefore a ton of heat
Dialogue: 1,0:06:20.98,0:06:27.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最烫的时候甚至能烧到1650°C！
Dialogue: 2,0:06:20.98,0:06:27.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Orbiter will reach temperatures of 1650 degrees Celsius or 3000 degrees Fahrenheit!
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.16,0:06:28.99,1080CN,,0,0,0,,烫烫烫
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.16,0:06:28.99,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.99,0:06:32.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但还好航天飞机真的很耐操，有4套不同的隔热系统
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.99,0:06:32.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But luckily, the Orbiter is covered with four different types of thermal protection
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.96,0:06:36.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一是机翼前缘强化碳-碳复合材料
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.96,0:06:36.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It has reinforced carbon-carbon on the leading edges
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.52,0:06:43.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,二是机腹与前部安装的共计24177到31088块不等的绝热瓦
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.52,0:06:43.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,then there were between 24177 and 31088 tiles, depending on the Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:06:43.82,0:06:45.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这个数字取决于机型
Dialogue: 2,0:06:43.82,0:06:45.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,on the underside and front of the vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:06:45.96,0:06:50.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,三是上舱门、上翼面与机身会用白色Nomex绝热毯覆盖
Dialogue: 2,0:06:45.96,0:06:50.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,then there is white Nomex blankets on the upper payload bay doors, the upper wing and fuselage
Dialogue: 1,0:06:50.92,0:06:54.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后是一些同为白色的表面绝热瓦用于隔绝相对较低的温度
Dialogue: 2,0:06:50.92,0:06:54.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and a few white surface tiles for low temperature areas as well
Dialogue: 1,0:06:54.51,0:06:58.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到着陆前最后12分钟，航天飞机表面会被炽热的电离气体覆盖
Dialogue: 2,0:06:54.51,0:06:58.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,For 12 minutes, the shuttle had so much hot ionized gases
Dialogue: 1,0:06:58.88,0:07:02.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这就导致完全无法与外界通信，也就是所谓的黑障
Dialogue: 2,0:06:58.88,0:07:02.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,surrounding the vehicle, it caused a full radio blackout
Dialogue: 1,0:07:02.51,0:07:05.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在空气摩擦的作用下
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.51,0:07:05.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Eventually, after several minutes of atmospheric drag
Dialogue: 1,0:07:05.50,0:07:07.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,配合精妙计算得出的S型飞行轨迹
Dialogue: 2,0:07:05.50,0:07:07.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and some computer guided S-turns
Dialogue: 1,0:07:07.69,0:07:10.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机靠这样才能减到比较正常的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:07:07.69,0:07:10.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the shuttle bleeds off a lot of its velocity
Dialogue: 1,0:07:10.44,0:07:13.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,同时，一旦高度降低到40千米以下
Dialogue: 2,0:07:10.44,0:07:13.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Once it's about 40 kilometers or 25 miles downrange
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.52,0:07:16.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,飞机会调整为20度俯角
Dialogue: 2,0:07:13.52,0:07:16.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the commander drops the nose to minus 20 degrees
Dialogue: 1,0:07:16.47,0:07:19.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,没概念的话，这是正常客机的近7倍
Dialogue: 2,0:07:16.47,0:07:19.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that's almost seven times steeper than a commercial airliner
Dialogue: 1,0:07:19.56,0:07:22.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而速度则快了20倍！
Dialogue: 2,0:07:19.56,0:07:22.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and it's still traveling 20 times faster
Dialogue: 1,0:07:22.67,0:07:27.30,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过最后落地的姿势倒是没太大区别，速度只稍微快了一点点
Dialogue: 2,0:07:22.67,0:07:27.30,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Finally the shuttle lands like a traditional jetliner only a little quicker
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.30,0:07:35.66,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到了350km/h，而跑道也足足有4.5千米长
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.30,0:07:35.66,1080EN,,0,0,0,,touching down at 350 kilometers an hour or 220 miles an hour on a 4.5 kilometer or 2.8 mile long runway
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.66,0:07:41.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这长度，光是因为地球表面弧度
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.66,0:07:41.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That runway's actually so long that there's over a one and a half meter or over 5 feet in relative height difference
Dialogue: 1,0:07:41.82,0:07:45.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就已经造成超过1.5米的高度差了！
Dialogue: 2,0:07:41.82,0:07:45.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,between the ends of the runway due to the curve of the Earth!
Dialogue: 1,0:07:45.07,0:07:46.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,流批吧
Dialogue: 2,0:07:45.07,0:07:46.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That's crazy
Dialogue: 1,0:07:46.87,0:07:49.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,欢迎回家!
Dialogue: 2,0:07:46.87,0:07:49.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It's quite the journey! Welcome home, Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:07:49.20,0:07:52.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,让我们再回来看看50年之后猎鹰九号的回收方式
Dialogue: 2,0:07:49.20,0:07:52.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So now, let's do a quick rundown on how a Falcon 9 is recovered
Dialogue: 1,0:07:52.64,0:07:55.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然我已经有说过好几次了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:52.64,0:07:55.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I've covered this topic a few times, more in depth
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.40,0:07:57.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果还有哪里不懂的话
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.40,0:07:57.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so if you have any questions remaining
Dialogue: 1,0:07:57.08,0:08:00.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我再次建议你看看我的过往视频《太空叉如何回收猎鹰九号》
Dialogue: 2,0:07:57.08,0:08:00.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,check out my video How SpaceX lands the Falcon 9
Dialogue: 1,0:08:00.42,0:08:04.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,升空约2分40秒之后，一级关机
Dialogue: 2,0:08:00.42,0:08:04.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,At around two minutes and 40 seconds into flight the Falcon 9 shuts down its main engines
Dialogue: 1,0:08:04.69,0:08:07.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也就是经常听到的MECO
Dialogue: 2,0:08:04.69,0:08:07.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,called MECO or main engine cut off
Dialogue: 1,0:08:07.07,0:08:08.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,继续滑行一小段时间之后
Dialogue: 2,0:08:07.07,0:08:08.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It coasts for a moment
Dialogue: 1,0:08:08.32,0:08:12.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一级会与二级分离
Dialogue: 2,0:08:08.32,0:08:12.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and then the first stage lets go of the second stage for stage separation
Dialogue: 1,0:08:12.11,0:08:17.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这时候就已经达到最大8000km/h的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.11,0:08:17.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,At this point the Falcon 9 is traveling up to 8000 kilometers an hour or almost 5000 miles an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:08:17.44,0:08:20.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,与65千米的高度了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:17.44,0:08:20.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,at an altitude of 65 kilometers or 40 miles
Dialogue: 1,0:08:20.52,0:08:24.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果你还记得航天飞机那个固体助推器的话，那速度才到这一半
Dialogue: 2,0:08:20.52,0:08:24.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Quick note, that's about twice as fast as the Space Shuttle's rocket boosters
Dialogue: 1,0:08:24.61,0:08:26.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,接着，一级火箭会用其氮助推器做一个翻转动作
Dialogue: 2,0:08:24.61,0:08:26.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The first stage quickly performs a flip maneuver
Dialogue: 1,0:08:26.76,0:08:30.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尾部发动机向前
Dialogue: 2,0:08:26.76,0:08:30.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,with its nitrogen thrusters, to point its engines prograde
Dialogue: 1,0:08:30.01,0:08:31.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后，根据任务情况的不同
Dialogue: 2,0:08:30.01,0:08:31.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Then, depending on the mission
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.46,0:08:37.78,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一级可能会点燃其9个发动机中的3个来做
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.46,0:08:37.78,1080EN,,0,0,0,,boost back burn
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.78,0:08:41.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可是万一剩下的燃料不是很够
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.78,0:08:41.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But there might not be enough margins left over to do the boost back burn
Dialogue: 1,0:08:41.90,0:08:49.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就只好跳过这个步骤，让一级凭借惯性继续向上滑行
Dialogue: 2,0:08:41.90,0:08:49.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In {\fs30}that case it's omitted and the Falcon 9 continues on its ballistic trajectory away from the launch pad and heads towards the drone ship
Dialogue: 1,0:08:49.29,0:08:52.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,至于具体采用哪种方式，在每次任务的页面上都有写
Dialogue: 2,0:08:49.29,0:08:52.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that's been precisely placed based on each mission profile
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.65,0:08:53.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过不管怎样
Dialogue: 2,0:08:52.65,0:08:53.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But in either case
Dialogue: 1,0:08:53.75,0:08:56.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这个助推器都会向上一直冲到
Dialogue: 2,0:08:53.75,0:08:56.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the booster will coast up to its highest point
Dialogue: 1,0:08:56.12,0:08:59.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,高度为100千米的卡门线以上
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.12,0:08:59.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,typically over the Karman line or 100 kilometers or 62 miles
Dialogue: 1,0:08:59.68,0:09:00.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,换言之
Dialogue: 2,0:08:59.68,0:09:00.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In other words
Dialogue: 1,0:09:00.57,0:09:04.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,至少有那么一瞬间，助推器会冲出大气层之外！
Dialogue: 2,0:09:00.57,0:09:04.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the booster gets to hang out in space for a minute or so!
Dialogue: 1,0:09:04.61,0:09:06.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不知道啥时候我也能去啊
Dialogue: 2,0:09:04.61,0:09:06.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Lucky, I wanna go
Dialogue: 1,0:09:06.10,0:09:08.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,等到助推器再入大气层
Dialogue: 2,0:09:06.10,0:09:08.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Around 55 kilometers or 34 miles in altitude
Dialogue: 1,0:09:08.95,0:09:12.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,下落到大概海拔55千米高的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:09:08.95,0:09:12.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the Falcon 9 will light up three of its nine Merlin engines
Dialogue: 1,0:09:12.13,0:09:14.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号的3发引擎会重新点火（reentry burn）
Dialogue: 2,0:09:12.13,0:09:14.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as it reenters the atmosphere
Dialogue: 1,0:09:14.08,0:09:15.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以此来降低下落速度
Dialogue: 2,0:09:14.08,0:09:15.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It does this to slow itself down
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.89,0:09:19.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,同时还会形成一个力场
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.89,0:09:19.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and it actually creates a literal force field around itself
Dialogue: 1,0:09:19.69,0:09:21.43,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以保证助推器不会在载入过程中烧毁
Dialogue: 2,0:09:19.69,0:09:21.43,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so it can survive reentry
Dialogue: 1,0:09:21.43,0:09:23.83,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在完成大约20秒的再入点火之后
Dialogue: 2,0:09:21.43,0:09:23.83,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After around 20 seconds of reentry burn
Dialogue: 1,0:09:23.83,0:09:26.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,助推器能减掉其30%到40%的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:09:23.83,0:09:26.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the booster scrubs off 30 to 40% of its velocity
Dialogue: 1,0:09:26.94,0:09:29.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样，下落过程中摩擦生的热就不会再对机身构成任何威胁了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:26.94,0:09:29.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which is enough to withstand the remaining heat
Dialogue: 1,0:09:29.11,0:09:31.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,再往后，原本稀薄的大气变得越来越浓厚
Dialogue: 2,0:09:29.11,0:09:31.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as the atmosphere gets thicker and thicker
Dialogue: 1,0:09:31.10,0:09:35.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,助推器将借此减掉剩下那60%到70%的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:09:31.10,0:09:35.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The atmosphere will then take off another 60 to 70% of the remaining velocity
Dialogue: 1,0:09:35.70,0:09:41.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后，到只剩下约1000km/h的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:09:35.70,0:09:41.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,until the booster is only traveling about 1000 kilometers an hour or 620 miles an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:09:41.27,0:09:45.86,1080CN,,0,0,0,,火箭会点燃1或者3个Merlin发动机, 进行最终的着陆点火
Dialogue: 2,0:09:41.27,0:09:45.86,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Then it lights up one or three of its Merlin engines to perform the final landing burn
Dialogue: 1,0:09:45.86,0:09:47.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这一步需要非常精准的时间控制
Dialogue: 2,0:09:45.86,0:09:47.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which it needs to time perfectly
Dialogue: 1,0:09:47.89,0:09:52.30,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为就算只开一个发动机，还保持着最小的推力
Dialogue: 2,0:09:47.89,0:09:52.30,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Even with just one of the nine engines running at its minimum throttle
Dialogue: 1,0:09:52.30,0:09:55.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这也远比火箭本身重力高太多了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.30,0:09:55.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the booster still has too much thrust to hover
Dialogue: 1,0:09:55.25,0:09:58.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,结果就是，如果点火太早
Dialogue: 2,0:09:55.25,0:09:58.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So if the vehicle stops before it hits the ground
Dialogue: 1,0:09:58.10,0:10:00.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,火箭就会再一次飞走
Dialogue: 2,0:09:58.10,0:10:00.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it'll actually start going back up
Dialogue: 1,0:10:02.29,0:10:04.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那还回收个毛线
Dialogue: 2,0:10:02.29,0:10:04.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's not good
Dialogue: 1,0:10:04.52,0:10:06.30,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这个精确操控时间的机制
Dialogue: 2,0:10:04.52,0:10:06.30,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This needs to be perfectly timed
Dialogue: 1,0:10:06.30,0:10:09.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,被叫做hover-slam或者suicide burn
Dialogue: 2,0:10:06.30,0:10:09.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in a maneuver called the hover-slam or suicide burn
Dialogue: 1,0:10:09.33,0:10:14.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,下面的步骤你们也知道，放腿，然后轻轻触地……
Dialogue: 2,0:10:09.33,0:10:14.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Then the landing legs deploy and the Falcon 9 softly touches down
Dialogue: 1,0:10:14.28,0:10:15.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然我们都有不顺利的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:10:14.28,0:10:15.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Well, hopefully
Dialogue: 1,0:10:21.07,0:10:25.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这时候就有人会问了，为啥太空叉就不能学学航天飞机的助推器
Dialogue: 2,0:10:21.07,0:10:25.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So before we move on, let's really quick remind you why the Falcon 9 doesn't use parachutes?
Dialogue: 1,0:10:25.87,0:10:28.43,1080CN,,0,0,0,,多少用一下降落伞啊？
Dialogue: 2,0:10:25.87,0:10:28.43,1080EN,,0,0,0,,like the Space Shuttle SRBs did
Dialogue: 1,0:10:28.43,0:10:29.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不用当然有不用的理由
Dialogue: 2,0:10:28.43,0:10:29.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Well there's a few reasons
Dialogue: 1,0:10:29.91,0:10:31.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我已经做了好几个相关的视频
Dialogue: 2,0:10:29.91,0:10:31.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and I'm just gonna breeze through these
Dialogue: 1,0:10:31.36,0:10:33.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以这里就简单罗列一下
Dialogue: 2,0:10:31.36,0:10:33.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,since I've done many videos about this
Dialogue: 1,0:10:33.65,0:10:35.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但将来有机会的话
Dialogue: 2,0:10:33.65,0:10:35.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and I probably still need to do
Dialogue: 1,0:10:35.23,0:10:37.66,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可能还会有更深入地讲解
Dialogue: 2,0:10:35.23,0:10:37.66,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a more dedicated and updated video about it
Dialogue: 1,0:10:37.66,0:10:40.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,Everyday Astronaut理论课堂之
Dialogue: 2,0:10:37.66,0:10:40.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So here's Everyday Astronaut's top seven reasons
Dialogue: 1,0:10:40.62,0:10:43.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号不用降落伞回收的七大理由！
Dialogue: 2,0:10:40.62,0:10:43.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,why SpaceX doesn't use parachutes to land the Falcon 9!
Dialogue: 1,0:10:43.88,0:10:45.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先，人家并不是没用过
Dialogue: 2,0:10:43.88,0:10:45.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,One: SpaceX tried to use parachutes
Dialogue: 1,0:10:45.71,0:10:48.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最初两次回收任务就是用的降落伞
Dialogue: 2,0:10:45.71,0:10:48.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,on the first two Falcon 9 missions to recover the booster
Dialogue: 1,0:10:48.55,0:10:51.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但是你想想，这玩意可是有航天飞机助推器两倍的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:10:48.55,0:10:51.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, the booster is going about twice as fast as the SRBs
Dialogue: 1,0:10:51.76,0:10:54.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,降落伞哪那么简单就承受得了呢
Dialogue: 2,0:10:51.76,0:10:54.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the parachutes couldn't survive the extra forces
Dialogue: 1,0:10:54.16,0:10:57.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第二，既然火箭本身已经有发动机了
Dialogue: 2,0:10:54.16,0:10:57.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Two: The rocket already has engines capable of slowing down
Dialogue: 1,0:10:57.51,0:10:58.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,干嘛放着不用啊？
Dialogue: 2,0:10:57.51,0:10:58.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,why not use them?
Dialogue: 1,0:10:58.82,0:11:00.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你见过哪个直升机还需要降落伞来降落的么？
Dialogue: 2,0:10:58.82,0:11:00.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Does a helicopter need a parachute to land?
Dialogue: 1,0:11:00.92,0:11:03.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为直升机有螺旋桨有发动机啊！
Dialogue: 2,0:11:00.92,0:11:03.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,No it has an engine and a propeller already!
Dialogue: 1,0:11:03.29,0:11:04.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第三，太空叉的目标可是去火星啊
Dialogue: 2,0:11:03.29,0:11:04.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Three: You can't land a large rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:11:04.87,0:11:06.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就算降落伞成熟了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:04.87,0:11:06.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,on Mars or the moon with a parachute
Dialogue: 1,0:11:06.61,0:11:09.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到了火星到了月球也完全没用
Dialogue: 2,0:11:06.61,0:11:09.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the atmosphere is too thin or nonexistent
Dialogue: 1,0:11:09.00,0:11:11.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不如选个比较通用的方案
Dialogue: 2,0:11:09.00,0:11:11.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So you'd better start practicing propulsive landings now
Dialogue: 1,0:11:11.62,0:11:12.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,直接精通，一步到位
Dialogue: 2,0:11:11.62,0:11:12.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and get good at 'em!
Dialogue: 1,0:11:12.45,0:11:14.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第四，一个比较关键的问题是，猎鹰九号最高点会冲到大气层之外
Dialogue: 2,0:11:12.45,0:11:14.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Four: The rocket needs to slow down
Dialogue: 1,0:11:14.01,0:11:16.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以这个速度再入大气层的话，本身就是一个问题
Dialogue: 2,0:11:14.01,0:11:16.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,before it hits the atmosphere to survive reentry anyway
Dialogue: 1,0:11:16.32,0:11:18.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因此必须在再入之前就开始减速
Dialogue: 2,0:11:16.32,0:11:18.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Remember that whole reentry burn thing?
Dialogue: 1,0:11:18.42,0:11:21.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而降落伞在大气层之外可没啥效果
Dialogue: 2,0:11:18.42,0:11:21.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a parachute can't work very well before it's in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 1,0:11:21.69,0:11:23.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可以说直接用火箭发动机减速是唯一可行的途径了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:21.69,0:11:23.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so rocket engines are the only way to go
Dialogue: 1,0:11:23.88,0:11:25.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第五，降落伞和其附带的一系列系统
Dialogue: 2,0:11:23.88,0:11:25.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Five: Parachutes and the supporting system
Dialogue: 1,0:11:25.73,0:11:26.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会必然地使箭身更长
Dialogue: 2,0:11:25.73,0:11:26.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that would allow the fuselage
Dialogue: 1,0:11:26.87,0:11:28.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也不可避免得增加了死重
Dialogue: 2,0:11:26.87,0:11:28.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to get stretched and not just compressed
Dialogue: 1,0:11:28.53,0:11:30.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并不是更经济的方案
Dialogue: 2,0:11:28.53,0:11:30.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,would just add otherwise dead weight
Dialogue: 1,0:11:30.54,0:11:32.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第六，虽然降落伞也不是不能控制
Dialogue: 2,0:11:30.54,0:11:32.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Six: Parachutes, although steerable
Dialogue: 1,0:11:32.71,0:11:34.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但相比柵格翼、低温气体推进器或者万向发动机支撑架
Dialogue: 2,0:11:32.71,0:11:34.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,are not nearly as precise as grid fins
Dialogue: 1,0:11:34.92,0:11:36.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那可完全不是一回事
Dialogue: 2,0:11:34.92,0:11:36.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,cold gas thrusters and an engine gimbal
Dialogue: 1,0:11:36.88,0:11:38.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,看看近期太空叉回收整流罩的情况
Dialogue: 2,0:11:36.88,0:11:38.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,SpaceX is finding this out the hard way
Dialogue: 1,0:11:38.90,0:11:41.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你就知道降落伞有多糟糕了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:38.90,0:11:41.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as they tried to catch their fairings under steerable parafoils
Dialogue: 1,0:11:41.58,0:11:44.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后一点，火箭这玩意不防水
Dialogue: 2,0:11:41.58,0:11:44.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Seven: Splashing down is bad mkay
Dialogue: 1,0:11:44.15,0:11:47.26,1080CN,,0,0,0,,液体火箭发动机泡盐水，你是要煲汤啊?
Dialogue: 2,0:11:44.15,0:11:47.26,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Salt water and precise liquid rocket engine don't mix very well
Dialogue: 1,0:11:47.26,0:11:50.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可以说，这是个非常重要的改良
Dialogue: 2,0:11:47.26,0:11:50.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So that's actually a great place to transition
Dialogue: 1,0:11:50.62,0:11:52.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到此，我们已经讨论了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:50.62,0:11:52.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Okay, so now that we recovered
Dialogue: 1,0:11:52.73,0:11:54.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机的回收部件
Dialogue: 2,0:11:52.73,0:11:54.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the reusable parts of the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:11:54.59,0:11:56.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以及猎鹰九号的一级
Dialogue: 2,0:11:54.59,0:11:56.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the first stage of the Falcon 9
Dialogue: 1,0:11:56.65,0:11:59.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,接下来，它们需要怎样的工序才能再次发射呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:11:56.65,0:11:59.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,what did they do to prepare them for reflight?
Dialogue: 1,0:11:59.48,0:12:00.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,先说说航天飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:11:59.48,0:12:00.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Let's start with the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:12:00.92,0:12:03.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,要把这家伙重新推上发射架
Dialogue: 2,0:12:00.92,0:12:03.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,What did it take to get one back to the launch pad?
Dialogue: 1,0:12:03.57,0:12:06.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第一件事是把掉水里的助推器捞上来
Dialogue: 2,0:12:03.57,0:12:06.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After splashdown, the boosters were sealed up
Dialogue: 1,0:12:06.06,0:12:08.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,先由潜水员把助推器的菊花塞上
Dialogue: 2,0:12:06.06,0:12:08.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,by scuba divers with a giant plug
Dialogue: 1,0:12:08.44,0:12:09.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后排空里面的水
Dialogue: 2,0:12:08.44,0:12:09.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,where they drained the water
Dialogue: 1,0:12:09.91,0:12:12.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样（水平漂浮的助推器）才能用拖船拖回肯尼迪航天中心
Dialogue: 2,0:12:09.91,0:12:12.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so it could be towed back to Kennedy Space Center
Dialogue: 1,0:12:12.10,0:12:15.74,1080CN,,0,0,0,,回收一个助推器需要18人才能完成
Dialogue: 2,0:12:12.10,0:12:15.74,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Each booster required a crew of 18 for ocean recovery
Dialogue: 1,0:12:15.74,0:12:17.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以每个航天飞机带两个助推器
Dialogue: 2,0:12:15.74,0:12:17.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Space Shuttle obviously had two boosters
Dialogue: 1,0:12:17.70,0:12:20.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,光是运回家就得36人了
Dialogue: 2,0:12:17.70,0:12:20.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so that's 36 people on booster recovery
Dialogue: 1,0:12:20.22,0:12:22.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后助推器会被拆开
Dialogue: 2,0:12:20.22,0:12:22.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Then the boosters are disassembled
Dialogue: 1,0:12:22.20,0:12:24.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,送往犹他州的普瑞蒙特瑞
Dialogue: 2,0:12:22.20,0:12:24.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and sent out to Promontory, Utah
Dialogue: 1,0:12:24.09,0:12:27.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,进行清理、重喷漆
Dialogue: 2,0:12:24.09,0:12:27.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to be cleaned, paint stripped, repainted
Dialogue: 1,0:12:27.22,0:12:29.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,详细检查与重新状态固体推进剂
Dialogue: 2,0:12:27.22,0:12:29.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,inspected and reloaded with solid propellant
Dialogue: 1,0:12:29.70,0:12:31.63,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后重新运回肯尼迪航天中心
Dialogue: 2,0:12:29.70,0:12:31.63,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Then they go back to Kennedy Space Center
Dialogue: 1,0:12:31.63,0:12:36.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在“美国装配与翻新站“进行组装
Dialogue: 2,0:12:31.63,0:12:36.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,for assembly at the United Space Alliance Assembly and Refurbishment Facility
Dialogue: 1,0:12:36.32,0:12:37.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,真是个贴切的名字
Dialogue: 2,0:12:36.32,0:12:37.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I like the name of that place
Dialogue: 1,0:12:37.69,0:12:39.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,火箭的四段
Dialogue: 2,0:12:37.69,0:12:39.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The four segments in each booster
Dialogue: 1,0:12:39.60,0:12:41.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,都会被换上新的点火器
Dialogue: 2,0:12:39.60,0:12:41.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,are then mated to a new igniter
Dialogue: 1,0:12:41.21,0:12:46.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,前段、头锥、尾裙部、锥台等乱七八糟的东西
Dialogue: 2,0:12:41.21,0:12:46.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,forward segment, nose cap, aft skirt and frustum, whatever that is
Dialogue: 1,0:12:46.52,0:12:50.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,基本上，真正“复用”的也就是外壳了
Dialogue: 2,0:12:46.52,0:12:50.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So basically just the casing was actually truly reused
Dialogue: 1,0:12:50.75,0:12:54.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以称之为翻新肯定来的更加准确
Dialogue: 2,0:12:50.75,0:12:54.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I definitely think refurbished is the right word here
Dialogue: 1,0:12:54.02,0:12:56.97,1080CN,,0,0,0,,把一个东西皮扒下来只剩骨头
Dialogue: 2,0:12:54.02,0:12:56.97,1080EN,,0,0,0,,considering they stripped it down to the bare metal each time
Dialogue: 1,0:12:56.97,0:13:01.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后再拿到一个翻新厂里去处理
Dialogue: 2,0:12:56.97,0:13:01.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and taken to a place called the Refurbishment Facility
Dialogue: 1,0:13:01.07,0:13:05.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这完全不是可复用吧！
Dialogue: 2,0:13:01.07,0:13:05.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the boosters aren't at all what I'd call reusable
Dialogue: 1,0:13:05.21,0:13:06.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,再来看看轨道器
Dialogue: 2,0:13:05.21,0:13:06.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but how about the Orbiter?
Dialogue: 1,0:13:06.95,0:13:09.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,助推器的翻新工程相比这玩意的可就是小巫见大巫了
Dialogue: 2,0:13:06.95,0:13:09.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,What's it take to actually get that thing reflying?
Dialogue: 1,0:13:09.60,0:13:10.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,降落之后
Dialogue: 2,0:13:09.60,0:13:10.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After touching down
Dialogue: 1,0:13:10.64,0:13:13.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会派出150位高级技工
Dialogue: 2,0:13:10.64,0:13:13.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a highly trained crew of 150 people
Dialogue: 1,0:13:13.00,0:13:15.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以及25辆高度定制的车辆
Dialogue: 2,0:13:13.00,0:13:15.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and 25 specially designed vehicles
Dialogue: 1,0:13:15.16,0:13:17.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,毕竟航天飞机这会儿没有动力开到停机坪
Dialogue: 2,0:13:15.16,0:13:17.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,head out to intercept the vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:13:17.03,0:13:20.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先排除潜在的爆炸与有毒气体
Dialogue: 2,0:13:17.03,0:13:20.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They do safety checks for explosives and toxic gases
Dialogue: 1,0:13:20.47,0:13:21.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后协助机组人员撤离
Dialogue: 2,0:13:20.47,0:13:21.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,helped the crew exit the Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:13:21.89,0:13:24.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后再把整架飞机拖进处理厂
Dialogue: 2,0:13:21.89,0:13:24.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and eventually they tow it to the Orbiter Processing Facility
Dialogue: 1,0:13:24.94,0:13:29.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后就在这个2700平方米的大机库里
Dialogue: 2,0:13:24.94,0:13:29.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Once inside the 2700 square meter or 29000 square foot hangar
Dialogue: 1,0:13:29.48,0:13:33.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,进行约125天的检修工作
Dialogue: 2,0:13:29.48,0:13:33.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the shuttle would be processed for approximately 125 days
Dialogue: 1,0:13:33.51,0:13:37.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会有超过115个多层平台参与工作
Dialogue: 2,0:13:33.51,0:13:37.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,More than 115 multi-level platforms would surround the vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:13:37.49,0:13:39.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,让工程师们得以检查其600万个部件
Dialogue: 2,0:13:37.49,0:13:39.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so engineers could check six million parts
Dialogue: 1,0:13:39.89,0:13:43.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,六百万！
Dialogue: 2,0:13:39.89,0:13:43.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Six million parts!
Dialogue: 1,0:13:43.31,0:13:44.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,搞没搞错？
Dialogue: 2,0:13:43.31,0:13:44.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 1,0:13:44.14,0:13:47.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但在此之前，还要先由技术人员穿着防护服去清理机身
Dialogue: 2,0:13:44.14,0:13:47.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But first technicians would don hazmat suits to clean the vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:13:47.67,0:13:50.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,去掉一切残余的有毒或自燃物质
Dialogue: 2,0:13:47.67,0:13:50.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,of any remaining toxic and hypergolic elements
Dialogue: 1,0:13:50.45,0:13:53.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,拆除轨道机动系统
Dialogue: 2,0:13:50.45,0:13:53.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Then they would remove the Orbital Maneuvering System pods
Dialogue: 1,0:13:53.21,0:13:55.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以及前向机动系统组件
Dialogue: 2,0:13:53.21,0:13:55.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the Forward Reaction Control Systems modules
Dialogue: 1,0:13:55.56,0:13:57.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,方便检修及测试
Dialogue: 2,0:13:55.56,0:13:57.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to be repaired and retested
Dialogue: 1,0:13:57.32,0:14:03.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后3个RS-25主发也得拆掉
Dialogue: 2,0:13:57.32,0:14:03.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Then crews would take off all three of the Space Shuttle's main engines, or RS-25's
Dialogue: 1,0:14:03.00,0:14:06.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其实就算放到今天，这玩意也是相当厉害的
Dialogue: 2,0:14:03.00,0:14:06.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,These babies are still incredible engines
Dialogue: 1,0:14:06.11,0:14:09.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可以说是有史以来最高效的型号了
Dialogue: 2,0:14:06.11,0:14:09.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,some of the most efficient engines ever made
Dialogue: 1,0:14:09.31,0:14:14.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但是每次发射之间都要进行巨额维护
Dialogue: 2,0:14:09.31,0:14:14.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But they required a healthy amount of inspection and refurbishment between each flight
Dialogue: 1,0:14:14.00,0:14:16.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,有五万个零件
Dialogue: 2,0:14:14.00,0:14:16.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Each engine had 50000 parts
Dialogue: 1,0:14:16.73,0:14:21.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其中约七千个还很容易坏，需要频繁换新
Dialogue: 2,0:14:16.73,0:14:21.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and about 7000 of which were life-limited and occasionally had to be replaced
Dialogue: 1,0:14:21.10,0:14:25.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到2002年的时候，肯尼迪航天中心接手了发动机的组装工作
Dialogue: 2,0:14:21.10,0:14:25.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In 2002, Kennedy Space Center took over assembly tasks of the engines
Dialogue: 1,0:14:25.23,0:14:27.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,终于不用为了翻新而运来运去了！
Dialogue: 2,0:14:25.23,0:14:27.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,instead of sending them out for refurbishment
Dialogue: 1,0:14:27.38,0:14:31.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但这还不是最要命的工作
Dialogue: 2,0:14:27.38,0:14:31.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But perhaps the biggest and most daunting task of the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:14:31.44,0:14:37.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,检修那几万块吹弹可破的隔热瓦才真是要命
Dialogue: 2,0:14:31.44,0:14:37.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,was inspecting the thousands and thousands of fragile silica tiles on the bottom of the Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:14:37.80,0:14:42.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,前面已经说过，一架航天飞机根据型号的不同
Dialogue: 2,0:14:37.80,0:14:42.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,There were between 24177 and 31088 tiles
Dialogue: 1,0:14:44.09,0:14:45.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会有24177到31088片绝热瓦
Dialogue: 2,0:14:44.09,0:14:45.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,depending on the Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:14:45.70,0:14:47.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,关键每一片长得还都不一样！
Dialogue: 2,0:14:45.70,0:14:47.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Every single one was unique
Dialogue: 1,0:14:47.82,0:14:51.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以必须逐个的仔细检查与置换
Dialogue: 2,0:14:47.82,0:14:51.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and had to be carefully inspected and if damaged, replaced
Dialogue: 1,0:14:51.60,0:14:54.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还有电子仪器、货仓
Dialogue: 2,0:14:51.60,0:14:54.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And of course, all the avionics, the payload bay
Dialogue: 1,0:14:54.94,0:14:57.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,液压操纵面、等等等等
Dialogue: 2,0:14:54.94,0:14:57.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the hydraulic control surfaces et cetera, et cetera
Dialogue: 1,0:14:57.59,0:15:00.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这么多东西都需要在每次飞行后被仔细检修
Dialogue: 2,0:14:57.59,0:15:00.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,were carefully checked out between each flight as well
Dialogue: 1,0:15:00.38,0:15:07.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这一系列算下来，每飞一次就得需要大概650000工时的检修
Dialogue: 2,0:15:00.38,0:15:07.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In total, the Space Shuttle required no less than 650000 hours of labor between each flight
Dialogue: 1,0:15:08.31,0:15:11.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,按普通人工资每小时25美刀
Dialogue: 2,0:15:08.31,0:15:11.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Say the average person made $25 an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:15:11.28,0:15:13.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那这样算下来
Dialogue: 2,0:15:11.28,0:15:13.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which I'm sure is kind of conservative
Dialogue: 1,0:15:13.33,0:15:15.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每次翻新光薪水就得付一千六百万！
Dialogue: 2,0:15:13.33,0:15:15.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,for a highly trained technician
Dialogue: 1,0:15:15.11,0:15:18.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,更别说这个价格其实非常保守
Dialogue: 2,0:15:15.11,0:15:18.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the cost of human labor to get a Space Shuttle ready for launch
Dialogue: 1,0:15:18.35,0:15:21.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为大家都是高级技工
Dialogue: 2,0:15:18.35,0:15:21.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,would be around 16 million dollars!
Dialogue: 1,0:15:21.45,0:15:24.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,薪水当然也在平均水平之上
Dialogue: 2,0:15:21.45,0:15:24.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And again, that's being fairly conservative
Dialogue: 1,0:15:24.60,0:15:26.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过早期情况也没这么遭
Dialogue: 2,0:15:24.60,0:15:26.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But it wasn't always this way
Dialogue: 1,0:15:26.18,0:15:29.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为一直到1986年，挑战者号事故之后
Dialogue: 2,0:15:26.18,0:15:29.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Actually, before the Challenger accident in 1986
Dialogue: 1,0:15:29.36,0:15:32.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机才开始被要求做严格的检修与翻新
Dialogue: 2,0:15:29.36,0:15:32.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the shuttle went through much less refurbishment and checks
Dialogue: 1,0:15:32.50,0:15:35.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以在那之前的话，问题也没严重到这个地步
Dialogue: 2,0:15:32.50,0:15:35.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So few in fact, it may have seen as little
Dialogue: 1,0:15:35.04,0:15:39.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,大概只需要相当于后来1%的工时就能完成了
Dialogue: 2,0:15:35.04,0:15:39.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as almost 1% the amount of labor hours between flights
Dialogue: 1,0:15:39.21,0:15:40.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,为了最大限度地避免挑战者号事故
Dialogue: 2,0:15:39.21,0:15:40.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But after the Challenger accident
Dialogue: 1,0:15:40.45,0:15:44.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA采用了更彻底的翻新步骤
Dialogue: 2,0:15:40.45,0:15:44.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA changed the entire process of getting the Space Shuttle flight ready
Dialogue: 1,0:15:44.56,0:15:49.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,检查变得十分复杂与精细，覆盖了从头到尾的每个角落
Dialogue: 2,0:15:44.56,0:15:49.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and wound up going over every single inch with a fine-tooth comb
Dialogue: 1,0:15:49.67,0:15:52.26,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过毕竟人命攸关的事，还是小心驶得万年船
Dialogue: 2,0:15:49.67,0:15:52.26,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That's probably a good thing when you're dealing with human life
Dialogue: 1,0:15:52.26,0:15:55.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,再往后，到了1989年
Dialogue: 2,0:15:52.26,0:15:55.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Oh and lastly, after 1989, to get the shuttle ready
Dialogue: 1,0:15:55.20,0:15:58.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA有了个叫OTS的76轮运输车
Dialogue: 2,0:15:55.20,0:15:58.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it was placed on top of the Orbiter Transfer System
Dialogue: 1,0:15:58.00,0:16:01.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,用来把航天飞机从轨道器处理厂
Dialogue: 2,0:15:58.00,0:16:01.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a 76 wheel transporter, to take it from the OPF
Dialogue: 1,0:16:01.59,0:16:02.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,运到装配建筑
Dialogue: 2,0:16:01.59,0:16:02.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to the Vehicle Assembly building
Dialogue: 1,0:16:02.95,0:16:04.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并在这里安装巨大的外置油箱
Dialogue: 2,0:16:02.95,0:16:04.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to be mated with the external tank
Dialogue: 1,0:16:04.32,0:16:05.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以及两枚固体助推器
Dialogue: 2,0:16:04.32,0:16:05.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the Solid Rocket Boosters
Dialogue: 1,0:16:05.65,0:16:10.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过呢，现在这个76轮大卡车已经属于太空叉了
Dialogue: 2,0:16:05.65,0:16:10.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Fun fact, SpaceX now owns the Orbiter Transfer System to transport their boosters!
Dialogue: 1,0:16:10.52,0:16:13.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那么，我们的主角
Dialogue: 2,0:16:10.52,0:16:13.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Okay, now time for the big question
Dialogue: 1,0:16:13.53,0:16:17.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号又要经过怎样的检修才能再次发射呢
Dialogue: 2,0:16:13.53,0:16:17.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,What does it take to get a Falcon 9 booster back to the launch pad?
Dialogue: 1,0:16:17.28,0:16:20.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,答案是，我不知道
Dialogue: 2,0:16:17.28,0:16:20.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Let me start off by saying a lot of this is speculation
Dialogue: 1,0:16:20.25,0:16:24.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为具体细节目前都还是保密的
Dialogue: 2,0:16:20.25,0:16:24.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,since SpaceX doesn't make public exactly what goes into preparation
Dialogue: 1,0:16:24.37,0:16:27.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过我们可以靠他们动作
Dialogue: 2,0:16:24.37,0:16:27.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but let's give a rundown on what they have done
Dialogue: 1,0:16:27.10,0:16:28.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以及置换的零件来做一些猜测
Dialogue: 2,0:16:27.10,0:16:28.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and what things they will be doing
Dialogue: 1,0:16:28.81,0:16:31.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先，如果是在水面上回收
Dialogue: 2,0:16:28.81,0:16:31.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So first off, if it landed on the drone ship
Dialogue: 1,0:16:31.37,0:16:33.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会有一个小型机器人出动
Dialogue: 2,0:16:31.37,0:16:33.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a little robot actually comes out
Dialogue: 1,0:16:33.02,0:16:35.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,立即固定住助推器
Dialogue: 2,0:16:33.02,0:16:35.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and grabs onto the booster and hangs on to it
Dialogue: 1,0:16:35.22,0:16:36.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,免得……
Dialogue: 2,0:16:35.22,0:16:36.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so this doesn't happen
Dialogue: 1,0:16:44.31,0:16:49.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后运输回来，大约只需要10位工作人员和两艘船
Dialogue: 2,0:16:44.31,0:16:49.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It's then transported back by a support crew of around 10 and two ships
Dialogue: 1,0:16:49.47,0:16:50.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果是在地面上回收
Dialogue: 2,0:16:49.47,0:16:50.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But if the booster lands on land
Dialogue: 1,0:16:50.96,0:16:54.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就会有吊车把推进器放上运输车直接带走
Dialogue: 2,0:16:50.96,0:16:54.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the booster is picked up by a crane and put onto their transporter
Dialogue: 1,0:16:54.25,0:16:56.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最初的几年里
Dialogue: 2,0:16:54.25,0:16:56.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,For the first few years of the Falcon 9 reuse
Dialogue: 1,0:16:56.96,0:17:00.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,回收来的火箭会被运往加州豪松市翻新
Dialogue: 2,0:16:56.96,0:17:00.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the booster were shipped back to Hawthorne for the refurbishment
Dialogue: 1,0:17:00.36,0:17:04.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过现在太空叉也有在卡纳维拉尔角建新的助推器翻新厂
Dialogue: 2,0:17:00.36,0:17:04.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But SpaceX is building a booster refurbishment facility at the cape
Dialogue: 1,0:17:04.53,0:17:05.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第一次成功回收助推器
Dialogue: 2,0:17:04.53,0:17:05.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The first booster to ever land
Dialogue: 1,0:17:05.93,0:17:09.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,是在2015年12月21日的OG2任务
Dialogue: 2,0:17:05.93,0:17:09.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,on December 21, 2015 for the OG2 mission
Dialogue: 1,0:17:09.91,0:17:12.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那枚火箭后来被彻底拆开研究
Dialogue: 2,0:17:09.91,0:17:12.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,was extensively torn down and inspected
Dialogue: 1,0:17:12.85,0:17:17.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,毕竟这还是太空叉第一次见到完整的火箭回来
Dialogue: 2,0:17:12.85,0:17:17.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Since this was the first booster that SpaceX actually caught in one piece
Dialogue: 1,0:17:17.44,0:17:18.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当然要好好检查一下
Dialogue: 2,0:17:17.44,0:17:18.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,they had to check their work
Dialogue: 1,0:17:18.70,0:17:20.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,看看是不是真的有完好地回收
Dialogue: 2,0:17:18.70,0:17:20.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and see if it actually came out okay
Dialogue: 1,0:17:20.98,0:17:25.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最初的13枚，或者说非Block 5火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:17:20.98,0:17:25.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On the first 13 reused boosters, or non-Block 5 boosters
Dialogue: 1,0:17:25.33,0:17:29.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我们能明显看出更换的有喷嘴后面的隔热盾与隔热毯
Dialogue: 2,0:17:25.33,0:17:29.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,we know SpaceX changed out the heat shields and blankets behind the exhaust nozzles
Dialogue: 1,0:17:29.80,0:17:34.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,有极其炙热的任务中烧毁的柵格翼
Dialogue: 2,0:17:29.80,0:17:34.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,We know they had to fix and repair the grid fins on the extra hot missions
Dialogue: 1,0:17:34.69,0:17:37.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我们也能看出他们也花了大量的时间检修
Dialogue: 2,0:17:34.69,0:17:37.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,We know they had to do a lot of inspections on the vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:17:37.57,0:17:39.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,更进一步他们还用X射线检查助推器
Dialogue: 2,0:17:37.57,0:17:39.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but they also had to run an X-ray along the booster
Dialogue: 1,0:17:39.93,0:17:42.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以保证箭身状态良好尚可用
Dialogue: 2,0:17:39.93,0:17:42.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to ensure the fuselage is still good to go
Dialogue: 1,0:17:42.49,0:17:43.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以让我猜的话
Dialogue: 2,0:17:42.49,0:17:43.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now I've heard speculations
Dialogue: 1,0:17:43.70,0:17:47.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,彻底翻修一下Block 3/4的一级
Dialogue: 2,0:17:43.70,0:17:47.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,of between 1000 to 10000 human hours of labor
Dialogue: 1,0:17:47.81,0:17:50.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,大概会需要1000到10000工时
Dialogue: 2,0:17:47.81,0:17:50.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,for the turnaround of the Block 3 and Block 4 boosters
Dialogue: 1,0:17:50.70,0:17:53.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但就算往大了说
Dialogue: 2,0:17:50.70,0:17:53.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And say this is terribly conservative
Dialogue: 1,0:17:53.15,0:17:56.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,假设需要100000工时才能搞定
Dialogue: 2,0:17:53.15,0:17:56.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Say it's actually 100000 hours of labor
Dialogue: 1,0:17:56.25,0:18:01.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那也还不到航天飞机轨道器的1/6啊
Dialogue: 2,0:17:56.25,0:18:01.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that'd still be over six times less labor than the Space Shuttle Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:18:01.48,0:18:04.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号从零件数量上就有相当优势
Dialogue: 2,0:18:01.48,0:18:04.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Falcon 9 has much less systems to check over than the Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:18:04.84,0:18:09.05,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以我应该可以确信猎鹰九号的翻新工程
Dialogue: 2,0:18:04.84,0:18:09.05,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so I think it's pretty safe to assume there's a lot less labor hours required
Dialogue: 1,0:18:09.05,0:18:10.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,远比航天飞机来的轻快
Dialogue: 2,0:18:09.05,0:18:10.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to prepare it for reflight
Dialogue: 1,0:18:10.27,0:18:13.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到了Block 5这代
Dialogue: 2,0:18:10.27,0:18:13.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,We know SpaceX has a goal with their new Block 5 Falcon 9
Dialogue: 1,0:18:13.72,0:18:17.66,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉的目标改为24至48小时内重新发射
Dialogue: 2,0:18:13.72,0:18:17.66,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to see it land and refly within 24 to 48 hours
Dialogue: 1,0:18:17.66,0:18:21.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每次飞行后只做保险性的检查
Dialogue: 2,0:18:17.66,0:18:21.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,with nothing but inspections and checks between flights
Dialogue: 1,0:18:21.34,0:18:26.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不做任何实际的维修与换新
Dialogue: 2,0:18:21.34,0:18:26.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The overall goal of their new Block 5 booster is to be reflown 10 times
Dialogue: 1,0:18:26.20,0:18:29.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就至少成功进行10次发射
Dialogue: 2,0:18:26.20,0:18:29.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,without any actual refurbishment, only inspections
Dialogue: 1,0:18:29.93,0:18:35.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,Block 5型是在先前的24个成功回收的基础上设计的
Dialogue: 2,0:18:29.93,0:18:35.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They built Block 5 having learned the lessons from the 24 recoveries leading up to Block 5
Dialogue: 1,0:18:35.33,0:18:38.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果你对更新历史有兴趣的话
Dialogue: 2,0:18:35.33,0:18:38.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,if you need a reminder of what's new with Block 5
Dialogue: 1,0:18:38.20,0:18:39.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我也有个视频说了相关内容
Dialogue: 2,0:18:38.20,0:18:39.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I have a video all about
Dialogue: 1,0:18:39.64,0:18:42.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,Block 5火箭及其改进之处
Dialogue: 2,0:18:39.64,0:18:42.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,what Block 5 is and what has changed
Dialogue: 1,0:18:42.50,0:18:45.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,初步罗列一下Block 5的更新
Dialogue: 2,0:18:42.50,0:18:45.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,A quick list of things that are new with the Block 5
Dialogue: 1,0:18:45.06,0:18:47.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,覆盖全箭身的隔热层
Dialogue: 2,0:18:45.06,0:18:47.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is a thermal protective coating on the whole booster
Dialogue: 1,0:18:47.54,0:18:49.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,发动机旁边的液冷隔热板
Dialogue: 2,0:18:47.54,0:18:49.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a liquid cooled heat shield by the engines
Dialogue: 1,0:18:49.77,0:18:53.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后新式的Octaweb布局，这一项大概提升了8%的推力
Dialogue: 2,0:18:49.77,0:18:53.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a bolted Octaweb, 8% increase in thrust on the first stage
Dialogue: 1,0:18:53.82,0:18:57.66,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还有升级的着陆腿，钛金柵格翼
Dialogue: 2,0:18:53.82,0:18:57.66,1080EN,,0,0,0,,upgraded retractable landing legs, titanium grid fins
Dialogue: 1,0:18:57.66,0:19:01.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,升级的复合材料容器2.0以及其他大量的改进
Dialogue: 2,0:18:57.66,0:19:01.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,an upgraded COPV 2.0 and a ton of tweaks
Dialogue: 1,0:19:01.37,0:19:03.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这就让火箭更加可复用了
Dialogue: 2,0:19:01.37,0:19:03.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that allow it to be even more reusable
Dialogue: 1,0:19:03.41,0:19:07.26,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这同时也是获得载人许可的一部分
Dialogue: 2,0:19:03.41,0:19:07.26,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and most importantly, rated for human flight
Dialogue: 1,0:19:07.26,0:19:12.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以为啥猎鹰九号就不用每次做大修？
Dialogue: 2,0:19:07.26,0:19:12.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So how can the Falcon 9 booster actually be reflown without refurbishment?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:12.52,0:19:13.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不用从里到外换个遍？
Dialogue: 2,0:19:12.52,0:19:13.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Can it?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:13.70,0:19:17.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到底是有多大的不同？
Dialogue: 2,0:19:13.70,0:19:17.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,What's so different about the Falcon 9 compared to the Space Shuttle?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:17.14,0:19:20.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我们先来跟固体助推器（SRB）比较一下
Dialogue: 2,0:19:17.14,0:19:20.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Well let's first compare it to the SRBs
Dialogue: 1,0:19:20.20,0:19:22.74,1080CN,,0,0,0,,找找差距到底在哪里
Dialogue: 2,0:19:20.20,0:19:22.74,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and see what it actually does differently
Dialogue: 1,0:19:22.74,0:19:26.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先，让SRB直接掉进大海
Dialogue: 2,0:19:22.74,0:19:26.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,First off, the SRBs splashed down in salt water
Dialogue: 1,0:19:26.32,0:19:28.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你觉得很省事吗
Dialogue: 2,0:19:26.32,0:19:28.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That's not really a good thing
Dialogue: 1,0:19:28.48,0:19:33.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,SRB大体上就是一个
Dialogue: 2,0:19:28.48,0:19:33.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Solid Rocket Boosters are also basically giant empty canisters
Dialogue: 1,0:19:33.00,0:19:35.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,塞满了橡胶质地推进剂的容器
Dialogue: 2,0:19:33.00,0:19:35.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that are loaded up with a rubber like solid propellant
Dialogue: 1,0:19:35.49,0:19:36.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每次飞行前重新填满
Dialogue: 2,0:19:35.49,0:19:36.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,between each flight
Dialogue: 1,0:19:36.40,0:19:39.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但液体燃料火箭发动机的话
Dialogue: 2,0:19:36.40,0:19:39.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is different than a liquid fueled rocket engine
Dialogue: 1,0:19:39.23,0:19:42.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就不是这么简单的东西
Dialogue: 2,0:19:39.23,0:19:42.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that has say tens of thousands of parts
Dialogue: 1,0:19:42.25,0:19:45.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一个有成千上万个零件的玩意掉进海里
Dialogue: 2,0:19:42.25,0:19:45.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,If a liquid engine were to be submerged in salt water
Dialogue: 1,0:19:45.94,0:19:47.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,啥结果不用我说了吧
Dialogue: 2,0:19:45.94,0:19:47.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I don't think that'd be a good thing
Dialogue: 1,0:19:47.28,0:19:49.99,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以，降落在陆地或者船上
Dialogue: 2,0:19:47.28,0:19:49.99,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So right there is probably the biggest thing
Dialogue: 1,0:19:49.99,0:19:55.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这可能就是最重要的一点了
Dialogue: 2,0:19:49.99,0:19:55.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,having a booster land on dry land or a dry ship deck is a huge leg up
Dialogue: 1,0:19:55.42,0:19:58.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,至少对复用性和翻新工程来说是这样
Dialogue: 2,0:19:55.42,0:19:58.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as far as reusability and refurbishment goes
Dialogue: 1,0:19:58.11,0:19:58.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,事实上
Dialogue: 2,0:19:58.11,0:19:58.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact
Dialogue: 1,0:19:58.94,0:20:02.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,与其把SRB拖回厂
Dialogue: 2,0:19:58.94,0:20:02.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the SRBs were so expensive to refurbish
Dialogue: 1,0:20:02.04,0:20:07.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,拆开来从头到尾翻新一遍
Dialogue: 2,0:20:02.04,0:20:07.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in the long run, it was more expensive to bring them back tear them down and all that
Dialogue: 1,0:20:07.27,0:20:09.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还不如直接造个新的呢
Dialogue: 2,0:20:07.27,0:20:09.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,than it was just to build new ones
Dialogue: 1,0:20:09.92,0:20:13.99,1080CN,,0,0,0,,再回来看看轨道器
Dialogue: 2,0:20:09.92,0:20:13.99,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So why is the Falcon 9 booster more reusable than the Orbiter?
Dialogue: 1,0:20:13.99,0:20:17.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先一个关键性的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:20:13.99,0:20:17.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Well first off, the Orbiter was not only a rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:20:17.61,0:20:21.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,轨道器是个7人太空船，而猎鹰九号只是个运载火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:20:17.61,0:20:21.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it was also a spaceship that carried up to seven people
Dialogue: 1,0:20:21.32,0:20:25.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这就让驾驶舱、太空船内部、货舱之类的
Dialogue: 2,0:20:21.32,0:20:25.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So a lot of work and check outs went into the cockpit
Dialogue: 1,0:20:25.58,0:20:28.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,都需要大量的检查与修理
Dialogue: 2,0:20:25.58,0:20:28.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the interior, the payload bay et cetera, et cetera
Dialogue: 1,0:20:28.92,0:20:32.19,1080CN,,0,0,0,,更别说那组火箭发动机了
Dialogue: 2,0:20:28.92,0:20:32.19,1080EN,,0,0,0,,let alone the actual rocket engine portion of the Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:20:32.19,0:20:34.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然RS-25至今为止都是相当先进的玩意
Dialogue: 2,0:20:32.19,0:20:34.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The RS-25 engine, although amazing
Dialogue: 1,0:20:34.84,0:20:37.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而且到后期也不再需要运到其他地方去维护
Dialogue: 2,0:20:34.84,0:20:37.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and eventually refurbished on-site
Dialogue: 1,0:20:37.01,0:20:40.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但还是需要非常可怕的工作量
Dialogue: 2,0:20:37.01,0:20:40.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,still required an awful lot of work to fly again
Dialogue: 1,0:20:40.32,0:20:42.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而太空叉的梅林1D发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:20:40.32,0:20:42.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Merlin 1D engine that SpaceX has developed
Dialogue: 1,0:20:42.81,0:20:45.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,已经点火超过5600次了
Dialogue: 2,0:20:42.81,0:20:45.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,has been fired over 5600 times
Dialogue: 1,0:20:45.90,0:20:50.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从设计出发点就有相当的不同
Dialogue: 2,0:20:45.90,0:20:50.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and is designed to be reflown and reused over and over with minimal inspections
Dialogue: 1,0:20:50.95,0:20:53.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然目前还没公布资料说到底需要多少的检修工作
Dialogue: 2,0:20:50.95,0:20:53.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,How much, we don't really know yet
Dialogue: 1,0:20:53.52,0:20:55.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过待会儿再讨论这个问题
Dialogue: 2,0:20:53.52,0:20:55.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but more on that in a second
Dialogue: 1,0:20:55.23,0:20:59.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但猎鹰九号和航天飞机最大的不同
Dialogue: 2,0:20:55.23,0:20:59.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But perhaps the biggest difference between the Falcon 9 booster and the Space Shuttle Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:20:59.70,0:21:02.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,是再入速度
Dialogue: 2,0:20:59.70,0:21:02.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is the velocity in which each one reenters
Dialogue: 1,0:21:02.50,0:21:07.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我们对比下SRB、猎鹰九号一级和轨道器的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:21:02.50,0:21:07.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Let's compare the velocities of the SRB, the Falcon 9 first stage and the Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:21:07.57,0:21:11.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,来让我们理解为什么它们有各自的再入系统
Dialogue: 2,0:21:07.57,0:21:11.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to help understand why each one uses their given reentry system
Dialogue: 1,0:21:11.38,0:21:15.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,SRB速度上限也就4800km/h
Dialogue: 2,0:21:11.38,0:21:15.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The SRB never exceeds 4800 kilometers an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:21:15.13,0:21:17.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而且也不会离开大气层
Dialogue: 2,0:21:15.13,0:21:17.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and it also stays lower in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 1,0:21:17.46,0:21:21.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因此也不需要为再入减速
Dialogue: 2,0:21:17.46,0:21:21.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so it doesn't require any kind of slow down before it reenters
Dialogue: 1,0:21:21.47,0:21:25.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,没出过大气何来“再”入？
Dialogue: 2,0:21:21.47,0:21:25.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,well because it never really exited in the first place
Dialogue: 1,0:21:25.29,0:21:26.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而对于猎鹰九号
Dialogue: 2,0:21:25.29,0:21:26.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Falcon 9 on the other hand
Dialogue: 1,0:21:26.50,0:21:28.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它最快能达到8000km/h
Dialogue: 2,0:21:26.50,0:21:28.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,goes from up to about 8000 kilometers an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:21:28.88,0:21:32.17,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最慢也有5000km/h
Dialogue: 2,0:21:28.88,0:21:32.17,1080EN,,0,0,0,,down to as low as about 5000 kilometers an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:21:32.17,0:21:35.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,用反推进技术帮助减速
Dialogue: 2,0:21:32.17,0:21:35.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in order to survive reentry using its retropropulsion
Dialogue: 1,0:21:35.84,0:21:38.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不出意外的话
Dialogue: 2,0:21:35.84,0:21:38.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But it's safe to say it will probably never see
Dialogue: 1,0:21:38.47,0:21:40.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以后的最高速度应该也不会超出8000km/h太多
Dialogue: 2,0:21:38.47,0:21:40.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,much more than 8000 kilometers an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:21:40.93,0:21:45.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,轨道器的再入就快得多了，速度有27000km/h
Dialogue: 2,0:21:40.93,0:21:45.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Orbiter reenters at speeds of up to 27000 kilometers an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:21:45.45,0:21:47.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但是它会在在上层稀薄大气中
Dialogue: 2,0:21:45.45,0:21:47.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but it slowly bleeds off a lot of its speed
Dialogue: 1,0:21:47.84,0:21:49.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,慢慢降低速度
Dialogue: 2,0:21:47.84,0:21:49.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in the upper atmosphere
Dialogue: 1,0:21:49.18,0:21:50.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你看
Dialogue: 2,0:21:49.18,0:21:50.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Wow
Dialogue: 1,0:21:50.01,0:21:53.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,速度上的差距是非常大的
Dialogue: 2,0:21:50.01,0:21:53.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Those are some pretty big differences in velocity
Dialogue: 1,0:21:53.08,0:21:57.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为猎鹰九号再入速度只有不超过8000km/h
Dialogue: 2,0:21:53.08,0:21:57.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Since the Falcon 9 booster reenters at only 8000 kilometers an hour
Dialogue: 1,0:21:57.47,0:22:03.05,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它经受的热量就只有轨道器的大概1/40
Dialogue: 2,0:21:57.47,0:22:03.05,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it experiences up to almost 40 times less heat compared to the Orbiter
Dialogue: 1,0:22:03.05,0:22:05.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,很奇怪对不对！
Dialogue: 2,0:22:03.05,0:22:05.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,What? How can that be?
Dialogue: 1,0:22:05.04,0:22:06.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我来计算一下给你们看看
Dialogue: 2,0:22:05.04,0:22:06.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Well, since the first stage of the Falcon 9
Dialogue: 1,0:22:06.90,0:22:10.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,8000+km/h这个速度最多最多也不过轨道器的1/3
Dialogue: 2,0:22:06.90,0:22:10.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,only gets up to at most about a third of orbital velocity
Dialogue: 1,0:22:10.71,0:22:14.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这一点就让其产生的热量远小于轨道器的1/3
Dialogue: 2,0:22:10.71,0:22:14.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it receives much less than just 1/3rd of the amount of heat
Dialogue: 1,0:22:14.37,0:22:17.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,运动物体迎风面产生的热量
Dialogue: 2,0:22:14.37,0:22:17.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The compressed gas on the leading edge of any vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:22:17.75,0:22:20.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,与速度是平方关系
Dialogue: 2,0:22:17.75,0:22:20.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,will see heat increase by velocity squared
Dialogue: 1,0:22:20.91,0:22:23.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但是传输到火箭上的热量就还要再乘个速度
Dialogue: 2,0:22:20.91,0:22:23.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but the thermal energy transferred to the rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:22:23.41,0:22:25.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也就是3次方
Dialogue: 2,0:22:23.41,0:22:25.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,goes as velocity cubed!
Dialogue: 1,0:22:25.46,0:22:28.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以如果什么东西运动速度变成了四倍
Dialogue: 2,0:22:25.46,0:22:28.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So that means if a vehicle is traveling four times faster
Dialogue: 1,0:22:28.72,0:22:32.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那这货前部就会烫64倍！
Dialogue: 2,0:22:28.72,0:22:32.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the bow wave in front can get 64 times hotter!
Dialogue: 1,0:22:32.09,0:22:36.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为速度是4倍，再*4，就是平方
Dialogue: 2,0:22:32.09,0:22:36.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,'Cause that's four times faster, times four, so squared
Dialogue: 1,0:22:36.34,0:22:40.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,再再*4，就是立方，得到64倍
Dialogue: 2,0:22:36.34,0:22:40.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,times another four, cubed, so 64!
Dialogue: 1,0:22:40.76,0:22:42.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然可能说的太简单了点
Dialogue: 2,0:22:40.76,0:22:42.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now this is an oversimplification
Dialogue: 1,0:22:42.72,0:22:45.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不过这也是为啥航天飞机会需要前缘的碳-碳绝热材料
Dialogue: 2,0:22:42.72,0:22:45.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but that's why the Space Shuttle needed those carbon-carbon leading edges
Dialogue: 1,0:22:45.82,0:22:48.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以及底部大量硅瓦
Dialogue: 2,0:22:45.82,0:22:48.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and those silica tiles all over the bottom of it to survive reentry
Dialogue: 1,0:22:48.82,0:22:50.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而且不管速度慢得多
Dialogue: 2,0:22:48.82,0:22:50.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but the Falcon 9
Dialogue: 1,0:22:50.58,0:22:54.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号还有一个再入点火的机制
Dialogue: 2,0:22:50.58,0:22:54.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,also does an a pretty significant retropropulsion burn
Dialogue: 1,0:22:54.04,0:22:57.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会进一步地减少火箭受到的热量
Dialogue: 2,0:22:54.04,0:22:57.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,before it reenters, to ensure the vehicle can survive
Dialogue: 1,0:22:57.14,0:22:59.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机没有这样的机制
Dialogue: 2,0:22:57.14,0:22:59.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Space Shuttle didn't do any of this
Dialogue: 1,0:22:59.18,0:23:01.63,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为它的底面很大
Dialogue: 2,0:22:59.18,0:23:01.63,1080EN,,0,0,0,,because it relied on its large surface area
Dialogue: 1,0:23:01.63,0:23:05.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在稀薄大气中呆几分钟的时间也能减少不少速度
Dialogue: 2,0:23:01.63,0:23:05.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to slowly bleed the speed off for several minutes
Dialogue: 1,0:23:05.34,0:23:06.17,1080CN,,0,0,0,,事实上
Dialogue: 2,0:23:05.34,0:23:06.17,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact
Dialogue: 1,0:23:06.17,0:23:08.66,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机要花掉接近10倍的时间
Dialogue: 2,0:23:06.17,0:23:08.66,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the Space Shuttle spent almost 10 times the amount of time
Dialogue: 1,0:23:08.66,0:23:10.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,来散发掉再入时产生的热量
Dialogue: 2,0:23:08.66,0:23:10.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,radiating heat off through reentry
Dialogue: 1,0:23:10.87,0:23:14.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这差不多也是其隔热盾的工作原理
Dialogue: 2,0:23:10.87,0:23:14.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which is the key to how its non-ablative heat shield worked
Dialogue: 1,0:23:14.31,0:23:15.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,总的来说
Dialogue: 2,0:23:14.31,0:23:15.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So long story short
Dialogue: 1,0:23:15.60,0:23:19.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,猎鹰九号首先再入速度很慢，不会产生太多热量
Dialogue: 2,0:23:15.60,0:23:19.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The first stage is going slow enough to not get crazy hot
Dialogue: 1,0:23:19.53,0:23:22.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以需要的绝热系统也很少
Dialogue: 2,0:23:19.53,0:23:22.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so it doesn't require nearly as much thermal protection
Dialogue: 1,0:23:22.77,0:23:24.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,应该可以说
Dialogue: 2,0:23:22.77,0:23:24.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Therefore it's probably safe to say
Dialogue: 1,0:23:24.96,0:23:28.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,只要不出岔子，这能避免大量翻新工作
Dialogue: 2,0:23:24.96,0:23:28.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it doesn't require as much refurbishment, hopefully
Dialogue: 1,0:23:30.79,0:23:33.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后再来说说我的想法
Dialogue: 2,0:23:30.79,0:23:33.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So some final thoughts on all this
Dialogue: 1,0:23:33.13,0:23:37.83,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先，为什么我觉得猎鹰九号不会走
Dialogue: 2,0:23:33.13,0:23:37.83,1080EN,,0,0,0,,First off, the reason why I think the Falcon 9 will actually achieve reusability
Dialogue: 1,0:23:37.83,0:23:39.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机彻底失败的老路
Dialogue: 2,0:23:37.83,0:23:39.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,when the Space Shuttle couldn't
Dialogue: 1,0:23:39.45,0:23:42.78,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其实首要的是工程理念差异
Dialogue: 2,0:23:39.45,0:23:42.78,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is mostly due to the engineering philosophy of SpaceX
Dialogue: 1,0:23:42.78,0:23:45.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉的火箭是长期进化的
Dialogue: 2,0:23:42.78,0:23:45.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They are constantly tweaking their rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:23:45.11,0:23:49.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,用其生产副总的话说
Dialogue: 2,0:23:45.11,0:23:49.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to the point where according to SpaceX's VP of production, Andy Lambert
Dialogue: 1,0:23:49.67,0:23:53.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,“太空叉从未制造‘两个完全相同的火箭’”
Dialogue: 2,0:23:49.67,0:23:53.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,SpaceX has "Never built any two vehicles identically
Dialogue: 1,0:23:53.47,0:23:56.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,“这就是太空叉的创新之处”
Dialogue: 2,0:23:53.47,0:23:56.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,"such is the pace of innovation at SpaceX."
Dialogue: 1,0:23:56.28,0:23:59.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而航天飞机就完全不是一回事了
Dialogue: 2,0:23:56.28,0:23:59.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now this is quite different from the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:23:59.07,0:24:01.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,总共也就5个能飞的
Dialogue: 2,0:23:59.07,0:24:01.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that had only only five operational vehicles
Dialogue: 1,0:24:01.81,0:24:05.39,1080CN,,0,0,0,,30年间基本上就没怎么更新过
Dialogue: 2,0:24:01.81,0:24:05.39,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that changed very little in their 30 years of operation
Dialogue: 1,0:24:05.39,0:24:08.17,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然航天飞机的第一版
Dialogue: 2,0:24:05.39,0:24:08.17,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact, phase one of the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:24:08.17,0:24:10.78,1080CN,,0,0,0,,再更新前也只飞了四次
Dialogue: 2,0:24:08.17,0:24:10.78,1080EN,,0,0,0,,was only the first four flights of Columbia
Dialogue: 1,0:24:10.78,0:24:13.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但再之后的改进就几乎没有了
Dialogue: 2,0:24:10.78,0:24:13.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After that, further development would be minimal
Dialogue: 1,0:24:13.35,0:24:15.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而猎鹰九号，如果什么设计没达到预期
Dialogue: 2,0:24:13.35,0:24:15.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But with the Falcon 9, if an idea doesn't work out
Dialogue: 1,0:24:15.88,0:24:17.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉完全可以在建造下一枚火箭的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:24:15.88,0:24:17.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,they can literally make that change
Dialogue: 1,0:24:17.55,0:24:20.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就做出修改
Dialogue: 2,0:24:17.55,0:24:20.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,on one of the next manufactured boosters
Dialogue: 1,0:24:20.09,0:24:21.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果是需要较大变动的话
Dialogue: 2,0:24:20.09,0:24:21.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And if it's a really big change
Dialogue: 1,0:24:21.31,0:24:22.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就放在下一Block实现
Dialogue: 2,0:24:21.31,0:24:22.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,they'll do that on the next Block iteration
Dialogue: 1,0:24:22.98,0:24:25.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,真要说的话，航天飞机也不是完全没改进过
Dialogue: 2,0:24:22.98,0:24:25.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Space Shuttle's design didn't exactly freeze
Dialogue: 1,0:24:25.81,0:24:29.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但其30年间那点进化
Dialogue: 2,0:24:25.81,0:24:29.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but it certainly didn't evolve nearly as much in 30 years
Dialogue: 1,0:24:29.69,0:24:32.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,实在是比猎鹰九号这8年来少太多了
Dialogue: 2,0:24:29.69,0:24:32.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as the Falcon 9 has in eight years
Dialogue: 1,0:24:32.21,0:24:35.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然这8年里有些设计也显得莫名其妙
Dialogue: 2,0:24:32.21,0:24:35.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Some might consider this much change reckless
Dialogue: 1,0:24:35.15,0:24:36.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但考虑到其最终目的
Dialogue: 2,0:24:35.15,0:24:36.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but considering the end goal
Dialogue: 1,0:24:36.81,0:24:39.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,是设计制造真正稳定可复用的火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:24:36.81,0:24:39.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is to actually have a reusable vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:24:39.44,0:24:42.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样一个激进的策略我真的觉得很棒
Dialogue: 2,0:24:39.44,0:24:42.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I'm really glad they're pushing this aggressively
Dialogue: 1,0:24:42.73,0:24:44.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我也完全不想再去等个30年
Dialogue: 2,0:24:42.73,0:24:44.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I just can't wait another 30 years
Dialogue: 1,0:24:44.80,0:24:46.79,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最后，如果有人说
Dialogue: 2,0:24:44.80,0:24:46.79,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And lastly to those that think SpaceX
Dialogue: 1,0:24:46.79,0:24:49.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉永远没法把复用成本降到能回本的程度
Dialogue: 2,0:24:46.79,0:24:49.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,won't be able to make it worth the cost of reflying
Dialogue: 1,0:24:49.56,0:24:52.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,或者质疑这样是不是真的有什么意义
Dialogue: 2,0:24:49.56,0:24:52.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,or who question whether or not it'll be worth it for them
Dialogue: 1,0:24:52.53,0:24:55.31,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这又关我们啥事呢
Dialogue: 2,0:24:52.53,0:24:55.31,1080EN,,0,0,0,,luckily for us, it really doesn't matter
Dialogue: 1,0:24:55.31,0:24:57.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉是个私企
Dialogue: 2,0:24:55.31,0:24:57.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,SpaceX is a private company
Dialogue: 1,0:24:57.14,0:24:59.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,影响他们抉择的主要因素当然就是能不能赚到钱
Dialogue: 2,0:24:57.14,0:24:59.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They will only do what makes the most financial sense
Dialogue: 1,0:24:59.98,0:25:02.86,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也许几年后他们会发现这确实回不了本
Dialogue: 2,0:24:59.98,0:25:02.86,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So if after a few years they look back and realize
Dialogue: 1,0:25:02.86,0:25:07.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,造个新的还是比较省钱省事
Dialogue: 2,0:25:02.86,0:25:07.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it's more expensive to try to refly these things than it is to make a new one
Dialogue: 1,0:25:07.12,0:25:11.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那为了赚钱大不了就不干了呗
Dialogue: 2,0:25:07.12,0:25:11.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they'll stop doing so because they don't wanna lose money
Dialogue: 1,0:25:11.08,0:25:13.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们没有任何义务去弄出可复用的火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:25:11.08,0:25:13.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They don't owe it to anyone to reuse their rockets
Dialogue: 1,0:25:13.98,0:25:15.61,1080CN,,0,0,0,,完全只是觉得有戏，觉得能省钱
Dialogue: 2,0:25:13.98,0:25:15.61,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It's only in their best interest
Dialogue: 1,0:25:15.61,0:25:19.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,觉得能让利益最大化
Dialogue: 2,0:25:15.61,0:25:19.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to figure out how to do so so they can maximize profits
Dialogue: 1,0:25:19.09,0:25:20.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这就很不同于航天飞机了
Dialogue: 2,0:25:19.09,0:25:20.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And that's just different than the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:25:20.81,0:25:26.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,后者承载着整个国家对可复用性的希望
Dialogue: 2,0:25:20.81,0:25:26.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which had the weight of the entire nation's expectations to be reusable
Dialogue: 1,0:25:26.07,0:25:29.74,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不管设计能不能达到预期效果
Dialogue: 2,0:25:26.07,0:25:29.74,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Whether or not the system put in place actually made sense
Dialogue: 1,0:25:29.74,0:25:30.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一旦弄出来
Dialogue: 2,0:25:29.74,0:25:30.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it was too late
Dialogue: 1,0:25:30.80,0:25:33.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就没有什么修改的空间了
Dialogue: 2,0:25:30.80,0:25:33.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,There was no room for major changes per say
Dialogue: 1,0:25:33.80,0:25:36.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,毕竟议会不懂这事，他们的耐心也很有限
Dialogue: 2,0:25:33.80,0:25:36.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,since Congress would probably frown upon
Dialogue: 1,0:25:36.36,0:25:39.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,“你看，这概念不行，还是别搞航天飞机了”
Dialogue: 2,0:25:36.36,0:25:39.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,"Well this didn't work out, let's scrap the entire idea."
Dialogue: 1,0:25:39.91,0:25:41.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以就我个人觉得
Dialogue: 2,0:25:39.91,0:25:41.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So personally
Dialogue: 1,0:25:41.01,0:25:44.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,现在这时代，到处都注重创新，材料科学也有长足的发展
Dialogue: 2,0:25:41.01,0:25:44.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I think with this new age of innovation and materials
Dialogue: 1,0:25:44.35,0:25:47.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,软硬件方面都在飞速进化
Dialogue: 2,0:25:44.35,0:25:47.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,rapid evolution of hardware and software
Dialogue: 1,0:25:47.13,0:25:50.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,领导也要求他们作出各种各样的尝试
Dialogue: 2,0:25:47.13,0:25:50.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and leadership that simply requires they keep trying
Dialogue: 1,0:25:50.23,0:25:51.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,直到达成目标
Dialogue: 2,0:25:50.23,0:25:51.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,until they figure it out
Dialogue: 1,0:25:51.53,0:25:54.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以我觉得我们已经有一只脚
Dialogue: 2,0:25:51.53,0:25:54.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I think we're finally entering a new era
Dialogue: 1,0:25:54.10,0:25:57.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,踏入可复用火箭与航天客机的大门了
Dialogue: 2,0:25:54.10,0:25:57.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,of reusable and airliner like rockets
Dialogue: 1,0:25:57.62,0:25:58.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,未来充满希望
Dialogue: 2,0:25:57.62,0:25:58.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Hopefully!
Dialogue: 1,0:26:00.80,0:26:02.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你们怎么想？
Dialogue: 2,0:26:00.80,0:26:02.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So what are your thoughts?
Dialogue: 1,0:26:02.76,0:26:06.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可复用是近在咫尺了
Dialogue: 2,0:26:02.76,0:26:06.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Is actual reusability finally upon us
Dialogue: 1,0:26:06.42,0:26:10.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还是认为太空叉不行人类药丸？
Dialogue: 2,0:26:06.42,0:26:10.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,or do you think we're still going to be stuck in refurbishment land?
Dialogue: 1,0:26:10.34,0:26:12.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果有任何问题的话
Dialogue: 2,0:26:10.34,0:26:12.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,What other questions do you have?
Dialogue: 1,0:26:12.02,0:26:14.99,1080CN,,0,0,0,,有什么见解、疑问、或者视频内容建议
Dialogue: 2,0:26:12.02,0:26:14.99,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Let me know your thoughts, questions, and video requests
Dialogue: 1,0:26:14.99,0:26:16.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,请在下面留言！
Dialogue: 2,0:26:14.99,0:26:16.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in the comments below!
Dialogue: 1,0:26:16.22,0:26:20.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,感谢来自kNews的Lukas提供这些动画
Dialogue: 2,0:26:16.22,0:26:20.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Lukas from kNews for his amazing animations
Dialogue: 1,0:26:20.46,0:26:21.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我一直很喜欢他的作品
Dialogue: 2,0:26:20.46,0:26:21.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,I've always been a fan of his work
Dialogue: 1,0:26:21.81,0:26:25.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也很高兴可以合作
